title: Summarise database characteristics
text: databaseCharacteristics() function provides comprehensive overview Common Data Model (CDM). returns summarised result combining several characterisation components: General database snapshot: Generated using summariseOmopSnapshot(), provides high-level metadata CDM, including size person table, time span covered, source type, vocabulary version, etc. Population characterisation: Describes demographics population observation, built using CohortConstructor CohortCharacteristics packages. Person table characterisation: Produced using summarisePerson(), component summarises content missingness person table. Observation period characterisation: Produced using summariseObservationPeriod(), component summarises content missingness observation period table. Temporal trends — including changes number records subjects, median age, sex distribution, total person-days — derived using summariseTrend(). Clinical tables characterisation: Produced using summariseClinicalRecords(), component summarises content missingness across clinical tables. Temporal trends number records subjects, median age, sex distribution also computed using summariseTrend(). Concept Counts: Optionally, concept-level summaries can included computing concept counts summariseConceptIdCounts(). Together, outputs provide holistic view CDM’s structure, data completeness, temporal behaviour — supporting data quality assessment study feasibility evaluation.
code: result <- databaseCharacteristics(cdm = cdm)

title: Summarise database characteristics
text: default, following OMOP tables included characterisation: visit_occurrence, visit_detail, condition_occurrence, drug_exposure, procedure_occurrence, device_exposure, measurement, observation, death. can customise tables include analysis specifying omopTableName argument.
code: result <- databaseCharacteristics(   cdm = cdm,    omopTableName = c("drug_exposure", "condition_occurrence") )

code: result <- databaseCharacteristics(   cdm = cdm,   omopTableName = c("drug_exposure", "condition_occurrence"),   sex = TRUE )

code: result <- databaseCharacteristics(   cdm = cdm,   omopTableName = c("drug_exposure", "condition_occurrence"),   ageGroup = list(c(0, 50), c(51, 100)) )

what: Filtering by date range and time interval

text: Use dateRange argument limit analysis specific period. Combine interval argument stratify results time. Valid values interval include “overall” (default), “years”, “quarters”, “months”:
code: result <- databaseCharacteristics(   cdm = cdm,   interval = "years",   dateRange = as.Date(c("2010-01-01", "2018-12-31")) )

title: Summarise database characteristics
text: can use sample argument limit characterisation subset CDM. can useful quickly exploring large datasets focusing specific cohort already included CDM. sample argument accepts either: integer, randomly sample specified number people person table CDM. string, corresponding name cohort within CDM use characterisation.
code: result <- databaseCharacteristics(   cdm = cdm,   sample = 1000L )  result <- databaseCharacteristics(   cdm = cdm,   sample = "my_cohort" )

code: result <- databaseCharacteristics(   cdm = cdm,   conceptIdCounts = TRUE )

code: shinyCharacteristics(result = result, directory = "path/to/your/shiny")

title: Summarise database characteristics
text: can customise title, logo, theme Shiny app setting appropriate arguments: title: title displayed top app logo: Path custom logo (must SVG format) theme: One available OmopViewer themes. background: custom background panel Shiny app example Shiny application generated shinyCharacteristics() can explored , characterisation several synthetic datasets available.
code: shinyCharacteristics(   result = result,    directory = "path/to/my/shiny",   title = "Characterisation of my data",   logo = "path/to/my/logo.svg",   theme = "scarlet",    background = "path/to/my/background.md" )

text: Finally, disconnect mock CDM.
code: cdmDisconnect(cdm = cdm)

title: Summarise the person table
text: summarisePerson() builds set common summaries: Number subjects: total number rows person. Number subjects observation: number (percentage) persons appear observation_period (useful detect missing observation periods). warning emitted found. Sex: counts percentages sex categories (Female, Male, Missing). separate Sex source table shows raw gender_source_value distribution. Race / Race source: distribution race_concept_id race_source_value Ethnicity / Ethnicity source: distribution ethnicity_concept_id ethnicity_source_value. Year / Month / Day birth: numeric summaries (missingness, quantiles, min/max) birth date components. Location, Provider, Care site: number missing, zeros, distinct values.

what: What are Event and Episode tables?
title: Summarise temporal trends in OMOP tables
text: Event tables capture occurrences happen single point time (example, diagnosis, prescription, measurement). tables, record linked time interval based start date. what: Tidy the summarised object with tableTrend
title: Summarise temporal trends in OMOP tables
text: tableTrend() helps convert summarised result nicely formatted table reporting inspection (example gt (default), flextable, reactable, DT::datatable). formats time intervals, strata estimate columns results easy read export. Summary Age years condition_occurrence, drug_exposure tables
code: result <- summariseTrend(   cdm = cdm,   event = "condition_occurrence",   episode = "drug_exposure",   output = "age",   interval = "years" ) tableTrend(result = result)

title: Summarise temporal trends in OMOP tables
text: plotTrend() builds ggplot2 visualisation summarised result.  result includes several outputs (example, records, persons, person-days), function defaults plotting number records. can override setting output argument measure want visualise.  can also specify facet (formula column) colour. Valid column names tidied result columns (see visOmopResults::tidyColumns())
code: result <- summariseTrend(   cdm = cdm,   event = "measurement",    interval = "quarters",   sex = TRUE,    ageGroup = list(c(0, 17), c(18, Inf)),   dateRange = as.Date(c("2010-01-01", "2019-12-31")) ) #> → The observation period in the cdm ends in 2019-07-03  plotTrend(   result = result,   colour = "sex",   facet = "age_group" ) result <- summariseTrend(cdm,   event = "measurement",   interval = "quarters",   output = c("sex", "record"),   dateRange = as.Date(c("2010-01-01", "2019-12-31")) ) #> → The observation period in the cdm ends in 2019-07-03 plotTrend(   result = result,   output = "sex" ) result <- summariseTrend(cdm,   event = "measurement",   interval = "quarters",   sex = TRUE,   inObservation = TRUE,   dateRange = as.Date(c("2010-01-01", "2019-12-31")) ) #> → The observation period in the cdm ends in 2019-07-03 plotTrend(   result = result,   facet = omop_table ~ sex,   colour = "in_observation" )

title: Summarise temporal trends in OMOP tables — summariseTrend
text: cdm cdm_reference object. Use CDMConnector create reference database omock create reference synthetic data. event character vector OMOP table names treat event tables (uses start date). episode character vector OMOP table names treat episode tables (uses start end date). output character vector indicating summarise. Options include "record" (default), "person", "person-days", "age", "sex". included, number person-days computed episode tables. interval Time interval stratify . can either "years", "quarters", "months" "overall". ageGroup list age groups stratify results . element represents specific age range. can give specific names, e.g. ageGroup = list(children = c(0, 17), adult = c(18, Inf)). sex Logical; whether stratify results sex (TRUE) (FALSE). inObservation Logical. TRUE, results stratified indicate whether record occurs within observation period. dateRange vector two dates defining desired study period. dateRange NULL, restriction applied.
